description: Fastighets AB Trianon engages in the ownership, management, development, and construction of residential and commercial real estate properties. The company is headquartered in Malmo, Skane and currently employs 67 full-time employees. The company went IPO on 2017-06-21. The company owns, acquires, develops and builds both residential and commercial premises in Malmo. The firm focuses on development of real estate in a way to create a modern office environment and to maintain cultural value. The Company’s portfolio consists of residential, commercial, office and community properties located in Malmo in the areas of City, Limhamn/Slottsstaden, Lindangen/Hermodsdal and Rosengard. In total, the Company holds more than 40 properties with area over 180 000 square meters. The project portfolio comprise more than 10 projects with area over 143 000 square meters. The Company’s main shareholders are Olof Andersson Forvaltnings AB, Briban Invest AB and Cedelma AB.
